gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 110, Grizzlies 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves win their third straight game and their eighth in the last 10 as they defeat the Grizzlies, 110-101. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 34 points and four assists as Naz Reid (19 points, six rebounds) and Karl-Anthony Towns (13 points, 11 rebounds) totaled 32 points. Jaren Jackson Jr. led the Grizzlies with 33 points and a career-high 13 rebounds as Ziaire Williams (16 points, eight rebounds) and GG Jackson (14 points, three rebounds) totaled 30 points. Minnesota improves to 42-17 as Memphis moves to 20-39.
